---
import Layout from '../layouts/SpotlightLayout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About" description="Cloud + AI tech lead building secure, compliant platforms">
	<section class="ascii-section">
		<p class="ascii-eyebrow">About</p>
		<h1 class="ascii-section-title" data-ascii-glitch>Paul Wen</h1>
		<p class="ascii-lede">
			I’m a software engineer and tech lead who builds enterprise-grade platforms across cloud and on-prem environments.
			I’m happiest owning problems end-to-end: shaping requirements, designing architecture, shipping code, and ensuring systems hold up under real-world constraints.
		</p>
	</section>

	<hr class="ascii-rule" />

	<section class="ascii-section">
		<p class="ascii-eyebrow">What I work on</p>
		<h2 class="ascii-section-title" data-ascii-glitch>Systems that need to be right</h2>
		<div class="ascii-surface" style="padding: 18px; margin-top: 14px;">
			<ul class="ascii-list" style="line-height: 1.85;">
				<li>
					<b>AI-assisted reporting & compliance workflows</b> — building retrieval-augmented generation pipelines with traceable inputs, strong access controls, and human review.
				</li>
				<li>
					<b>Workflow platforms for evaluation and governance</b> — replacing spreadsheet-heavy processes with role-based systems, auditable decision history, and clear dashboards.
				</li>
				<li>
					<b>Platform modernisation</b> — migrating legacy solutions to cloud-aligned, API-first architectures with CI/CD, quality gates, and pragmatic observability.
				</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
	</section>

	<hr class="ascii-rule" />

	<section class="ascii-section">
		<p class="ascii-eyebrow">How I lead</p>
		<h2 class="ascii-section-title" data-ascii-glitch>Delivery, clarity, and engineering discipline</h2>
		<p class="ascii-lede">
			I focus on building systems that teams can operate and evolve: clear boundaries, boring reliability, and security by default.
			I also spend a lot of time on requirements engineering—making trade-offs explicit and aligning stakeholders on what’s possible now vs. what’s next.
		</p>
		<div class="ascii-surface ascii-surface--muted" style="padding: 18px; margin-top: 14px;">
			<p class="ascii-muted ascii-mono" style="margin: 0 0 10px;">[ principles ]</p>
			<ul class="ascii-list" style="line-height: 1.85;">
				<li>Design for auditability and least-privilege access (RBAC, identity-first).</li>
				<li>Prefer simple, testable interfaces (APIs, events, contracts) over hidden coupling.</li>
				<li>Ship iteratively with strong CI/CD and production readiness checks.</li>
				<li>Keep the human-in-the-loop where it matters for safety and compliance.</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
	</section>

	<hr class="ascii-rule" />

	<section class="ascii-section">
		<p class="ascii-eyebrow">Toolkit</p>
		<h2 class="ascii-section-title" data-ascii-glitch>What I’m comfortable shipping</h2>
		<div class="ascii-surface" style="padding: 18px; margin-top: 14px;">
			<p class="ascii-muted" style="margin: 0; line-height: 1.85;">
				TypeScript/Node.js, React, REST APIs, PostgreSQL/MongoDB, Docker, CI/CD pipelines, and cloud platforms (Azure/AWS).
				For AI-enabled systems: RAG patterns, governance-aligned deployment, and review workflows that keep quality and traceability front and center.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<hr class="ascii-rule" />

	<section class="ascii-section">
		<p class="ascii-eyebrow">Contact</p>
		<h2 class="ascii-section-title" data-ascii-glitch>Let’s talk</h2>
		<p class="ascii-lede">
			If you’re building a platform where reliability and accountability matter, I’d love to help.
		</p>
		<div class="ascii-surface" style="padding: 14px; margin-top: 14px;">
			<p class="ascii-muted ascii-mono" style="margin: 0 0 10px;">[ channels ]</p>
			<div style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 12px;">
				<a class="ascii-mono" href="mailto:xiandepaul.wen@gmail.com">[ email ]</a>
				<a class="ascii-mono" href="https://linkedin.com/in/xiandew" target="_blank" rel="noopener">[ linkedin ]</a>
				<a class="ascii-mono" href="https://github.com/xiandew" target="_blank" rel="noopener">[ github ]</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>
